            <div class="info-box__title">📘 A. Explanation</div>
            <div class="info-box__content">
              <p><strong>New in 2021.</strong> This category relates to code and infrastructure that does not protect against integrity violations. Examples include using software from untrusted sources (supply chain attacks), insecure CI/CD pipelines, and auto-update mechanisms without integrity verification. Insecure deserialization (previously A08:2017) is merged here.</p>
              <ul>
                <li>Supply chain attacks on npm/PyPI packages</li>
                <li>CI/CD pipelines without proper access controls</li>
                <li>Auto-updates without signature verification</li>
                <li>Insecure deserialization leading to RCE</li>
                <li>Using CDN scripts without Subresource Integrity (SRI) hashes</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="info-box info-box--example">
            <div class="info-box__title">🟣 B. Real-World Example</div>
            <div class="info-box__content">
              <p><strong>SolarWinds (2020):</strong> Attackers compromised the SolarWinds build system and inserted malware into the Orion platform update. 18,000+ organizations (including US government agencies, Microsoft, FireEye) installed the trojanized update. The most devastating supply chain attack in history.</p>
              <p><strong>event-stream (2018):</strong> A popular npm package (2M weekly downloads) was hijacked when maintainership was transferred to a malicious actor who added code targeting the Copay cryptocurrency wallet.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

