    <!-- A09 -->
    <div class="accordion__item">
      <div class="accordion__header">
        <span class="accordion__id">A09:2021</span>
        <h3 class="accordion__title">Security Logging and Monitoring Failures</h3>
        <span class="accordion__arrow">▼</span>
      </div>
      <div class="accordion__body">
        <div class="accordion__content">
          <div class="info-box info-box--explain">
            <div class="info-box__title">📘 A. Explanation</div>
            <div class="info-box__content">
              <p>Without logging and monitoring, breaches cannot be detected. Insufficient logging, unclear log messages, logs not monitored or only stored locally, and lack of alerting allow attackers to further attack systems, maintain persistence, pivot to more systems, and tamper, extract, or destroy data.</p>
              <ul>
                <li>Login failures not logged or monitored</li>
                <li>Warnings and errors generating no log entries</li>
                <li>Logs stored only locally (lost on server compromise)</li>
                <li>No alerting on suspicious activity patterns</li>
                <li>No incident response plan in place</li>
                <li>Average breach detection time: <strong>287 days</strong> (IBM 2021)</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="info-box info-box--example">
            <div class="info-box__title">🟣 B. Real-World Example</div>
            <div class="info-box__content">
              <p><strong>Marriott International (2018):</strong> Attackers had access to Starwood's reservation system for 4 YEARS (2014-2018) before detection, compromising 500 million guest records. The breach went undetected because there was no monitoring for anomalous database queries.</p>
              <p><strong>Target (2013):</strong> Security tools (FireEye) detected the breach and generated alerts, but the security team ignored them. 40 million credit card numbers were stolen during the holiday season.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="info-box info-box--exploit">
            <div class="info-box__title">🔴 C. How the Exploit Happens (POC)</div>
