                  <span class="code-block__lang">Attack Timeline — Undetected Breach</span>
                  <button class="code-block__copy">Copy</button>
                </div>
                <pre><code># Day 1: Attacker performs credential stuffing
POST /login × 10,000 attempts → No logging, no alerts

# Day 5: Valid creds found, attacker logs in
# No anomaly detection for unusual login location/time

# Day 10: Privilege escalation
# Admin panel accessed → No access control logging

# Day 30: Data exfiltration begins
SELECT * FROM customers → 100,000 records/day
# No monitoring of large query results

# Day 60: Attacker sells data on dark web
# Company finds out from a journalist 💀

# Total detection time: 60+ days
# With proper monitoring: Could detect in MINUTES</code></pre>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="info-box info-box--remediation">
            <div class="info-box__title">✅ D. Remediation</div>
            <div class="info-box__content">
              <ul>
                <li>Log all <strong>authentication failures</strong>, access control denials, and input validation failures</li>
                <li>Ensure logs contain sufficient <strong>context</strong> (timestamp, user, IP, action, resource)</li>
                <li>Use <strong>centralized log management</strong> (ELK Stack, Splunk, Datadog)</li>
                <li>Set up <strong>real-time alerting</strong> for suspicious patterns (multiple failed logins, off-hours access)</li>
                <li>Implement a <strong>Security Information and Event Management (SIEM)</strong> solution</li>
                <li>Create and test an <strong>Incident Response Plan</strong> regularly</li>
                <li>Ensure logs are <strong>tamper-proof</strong> (append-only, separate storage)</li>
